1
00:00:15,041 --> 00:00:17,291
-Please have some.
-Oh, thank you.

2
00:00:18,833 --> 00:00:20,791
-For the conductor too.
-Oh, I couldn't.

3
00:00:20,875 --> 00:00:21,916
I insist.

4
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,750
In that case, thank you.

5
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,166
It's delicious.

6
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:39,500
Thank you.

7
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:40,833
Not a problem.

8
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,875
Oh, have some.

9
00:00:43,833 --> 00:00:45,416
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

10
00:00:58,583 --> 00:01:00,666
It's so pretty.

11
00:01:02,541 --> 00:01:04,333
I've never noticed the view before.

12
00:01:06,291 --> 00:01:09,250
I ride this line all the time,
but I never took a good look.

13
00:01:11,166 --> 00:01:12,583
I agree.

14
00:01:13,083 --> 00:01:13,958
Yeah.

15
00:01:14,041 --> 00:01:16,375
I've never gotten off here before either.

16
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,791
Maybe we were actually lucky.

17
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:26,333
The train stopped, we discovered this view

18
00:01:27,208 --> 00:01:29,583
and found a beauty that we'd never known.

19
00:01:51,708 --> 00:01:52,708
By the way…

20
00:01:56,916 --> 00:01:59,041
Haven't we met somewhere before?

21
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:09,416
What?

22
00:02:11,291 --> 00:02:13,500
Um, when could it have been?

23
00:02:13,583 --> 00:02:15,166
I don't believe we've ever met.

24
00:02:16,208 --> 00:02:18,125
Wait, we've never met?

25
00:02:18,208 --> 00:02:19,625
That doesn't seem right.

26
00:02:21,583 --> 00:02:23,083
Oh, I'll take that.

27
00:02:23,166 --> 00:02:24,000
No.

28
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:28,416
Wait, I apologize.

29
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,416
That wasn't my intention.

30
00:02:32,125 --> 00:02:33,875
-That's not--
-Where's the dish towel?

31
00:02:33,958 --> 00:02:36,125
Oh, the dish towel is over here.

32
00:02:36,208 --> 00:02:37,333
-Thank you.
-Here.

33
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:43,666
We're done here.

34
00:02:45,666 --> 00:02:48,208
Wait, I still wanted to talk about…

35
00:02:49,041 --> 00:02:51,750
Thank you for your kind patience.

36
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,666
I truly, sincerely apologize

37
00:02:53,750 --> 00:02:57,375
for making you spend
your valuable time waiting this morning.

38
00:02:58,208 --> 00:02:59,583
We will depart shortly.

39
00:03:05,416 --> 00:03:09,583
Also, to the passenger
who provided everyone with coffee,

40
00:03:09,666 --> 00:03:11,416
I truly appreciate it.

41
00:03:11,916 --> 00:03:13,958
It brought me to tears.

42
00:03:14,666 --> 00:03:16,625
Please board and wait for our departure.

43
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:17,833
Thank you.

44
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:19,416
Oh, it was nothing.

45
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:21,750
Thank you for the coffee.

46
00:03:21,833 --> 00:03:22,708
Thank you.

47
00:03:23,541 --> 00:03:25,583
-It was great.
-I'm glad.

48
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:26,583
Thank you.

49
00:03:59,333 --> 00:04:00,416
Good morning.

50
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,750
Good morning!

51
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:12,666
-Sorry I'm late.
-Let's get started.

52
00:04:12,750 --> 00:04:13,750
-Okay.
-Okay.

53
00:04:20,583 --> 00:04:22,333
Let's start with the dry beans.

54
00:04:22,416 --> 00:04:23,250
-Okay.
-Right.

55
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:36,833
Your opinions?

56
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,166
I liked the lightness of Number Three.

57
00:04:46,250 --> 00:04:48,416
It had a very refreshing finish.

58
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,750
Its unique aroma was nice.

59
00:04:50,833 --> 00:04:53,541
But I think it's a bit too bright.

60
00:04:54,291 --> 00:04:59,041
I think the slight depth
of Number One was nice.

61
00:04:59,125 --> 00:05:02,500
It had a rich sweetness
reminiscent of brown sugar.

62
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:05,666
I thought Number One had a nice depth,

63
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,500
but isn't it missing something?

64
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,416
Since it seems a bit flat,

65
00:05:09,500 --> 00:05:12,375
could we adjust the roasting time
to bring out its flavor?

66
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:14,208
This one's unusual.

67
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:17,333
It's really spicy and could be risky,
but it tastes good.

68
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:18,875
Well…

69
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:21,250
It's unique.

70
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:24,250
And it has a rich flavor.

71
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,333
It's hard to balance those two things.

72
00:05:27,416 --> 00:05:29,166
But you have the skills, Mr. Shinoda.

73
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:33,250
No, this isn't worth
sweet-talking me over.

74
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:36,541
If we can sell this,
it could be another signature product.

75
00:05:36,625 --> 00:05:38,208
I'm saying we can't sell it, moron!

76
00:05:38,291 --> 00:05:39,833
-Okay, if I may.
-Huh? What is it?

77
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:41,666
Let's go back to basics.

78
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:42,583
Huh?

79
00:05:43,625 --> 00:05:44,541
-Mr. Shinoda.
-Yeah?

80
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:48,166
Which flavor feels more like us?
Number One or Two?

81
00:05:53,416 --> 00:05:54,625
Probably Number One.

82
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:08,375
So you see,

83
00:06:08,958 --> 00:06:10,583
when I thought about it,

84
00:06:10,666 --> 00:06:15,083
the fact that he made coffee
and chatted with me isn't all that weird.

85
00:06:16,750 --> 00:06:20,708
I just got angry for no reason
when he sounded like Yusuke.

86
00:06:22,958 --> 00:06:23,875
I feel stupid.

87
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:25,708
I don't get it.

88
00:06:26,541 --> 00:06:27,750
Oh, really?

89
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:31,083
Yeah, he seemed like a great guy.

90
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:34,791
Man, I think I was out of line.

91
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:39,000
When he asked me if we met before,
I snapped and said, "No."

92
00:06:40,166 --> 00:06:43,666
It might just be
that I resemble someone he knows.

93
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:45,916
I mean, we ride the same train, after all.

94
00:06:47,416 --> 00:06:48,541
I see.

95
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:51,208
Yeah.

96
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:55,666
Sorry, I don't have any wisdom to share.

97
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,875
Lending an ear
is all you need to do, Kengo.

98
00:06:58,958 --> 00:07:01,125
Oh, so I'm just here to listen to you?

99
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:04,375
Yeah, we need listeners like you
in this world.

100
00:07:04,458 --> 00:07:06,708
If everyone on Earth
just talked all the time…

101
00:07:07,375 --> 00:07:09,500
Basically, if everyone were like me,

102
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:11,583
the world would be so annoying.

103
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:13,041
I'd hate it.

104
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:14,708
Oh, really?

105
00:07:15,291 --> 00:07:16,416
I guess it's fine then.

106
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,833
Yeah.

107
00:07:20,875 --> 00:07:22,000
But, you know…

108
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:25,750
You were Yusuke's listener too, right?

109
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:31,333
Were you like that since you were kids?

110
00:07:33,375 --> 00:07:34,208
More or less.

111
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,416
I see.

112
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,958
What's that?

113
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:09,333
Oh, wow.

114
00:08:15,375 --> 00:08:16,750
You know…

115
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,666
What?

116
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:20,458
I thought you'd only learned
to tolerate coffee,

117
00:08:20,541 --> 00:08:22,000
even though you don't like it.

118
00:08:23,375 --> 00:08:26,875
But judging from this,
you aren't just tolerating it.

119
00:08:27,666 --> 00:08:28,916
You like it now.

120
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:34,875
Oh, yeah. You might be right.

121
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:36,208
Yeah.

122
00:08:39,625 --> 00:08:42,000
I see. You like it, huh?

123
00:08:46,875 --> 00:08:49,583
-It's good to like new things.
-Yeah.

124
00:08:49,666 --> 00:08:51,125
It's wonderful.

125
00:08:56,416 --> 00:09:00,083
But I hope you don't start to hate
the things you used to love.

126
00:09:01,916 --> 00:09:02,750
What?

127
00:09:11,791 --> 00:09:12,875
That hasn't happened.

128
00:09:13,583 --> 00:09:14,416
It hasn't.

129
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:17,250
I am who I am.

130
00:09:18,125 --> 00:09:19,541
The things I love won't change.

131
00:09:26,208 --> 00:09:27,916
My favorite ramen is miso.

132
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:29,958
That won't ever change.

133
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:32,625
Was that the point here?

134
00:09:32,708 --> 00:09:34,833
I need sauce for my sunny side up eggs.

135
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:36,916
That won't change either.

136
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:39,666
Hayao Miyazaki likes them that way too.

137
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:40,958
-Oh, really?
-Yeah.

138
00:09:41,583 --> 00:09:43,041
Wait, who cares?

139
00:09:44,458 --> 00:09:45,708
Hmm, what else?

140
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:57,958
Maru Coffee!

141
00:09:58,041 --> 00:09:59,875
I thought it sounded cute.

142
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:01,750
It's so hip!

143
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:04,208
How trendy. Who came up with this?

144
00:10:04,291 --> 00:10:06,708
-Who was it?
-It was Yusuke.

145
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:09,791
Maru Coffee.

146
00:10:11,666 --> 00:10:12,916
The world is round.

147
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,750
-Yeah.
-Maru is "round" in Japanese.

148
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:18,625
Even if we end up apart,

149
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,083
we'll reunite eventually, you know?

150
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,083
That's what "maru" means.

151
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:24,625
The world is round.

152
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:27,291
-Hey!
-What?

153
00:10:27,375 --> 00:10:29,583
The moment you do that,
the coffee is ruined.

154
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:30,791
No way! This one's…

155
00:10:30,875 --> 00:10:32,666
-It's true. You…
-Stop that.

156
00:10:32,750 --> 00:10:35,416
-This is so good!
-It's tasty.

157
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,416
Really?

158
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:39,583
-Come on!
-All right! We did it!

159
00:10:40,458 --> 00:10:42,541
-We're just getting started.
-What?

160
00:10:44,125 --> 00:10:46,208
All right. Here it comes.

161
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:47,166
It's here!

162
00:10:47,666 --> 00:10:50,666
-There they are!
-Whoa, they're so big!

163
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:52,291
Fireworks are the best!

164
00:10:52,875 --> 00:10:54,083
The best!

165
00:10:54,166 --> 00:10:58,208
-And Saeko in a yukata is the best too!
-Woo-hoo!

166
00:10:58,291 --> 00:10:59,833
Hooray!

167
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:01,208
There's more coming!

168
00:11:02,958 --> 00:11:04,541
You'll get sunburned lying there.

169
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:06,750
-That's okay.
-You're okay with that?

170
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,083
I want to get a tan.

171
00:11:08,958 --> 00:11:10,041
Whoa, stop that.

172
00:11:10,125 --> 00:11:11,416
-That's dangerous.
-Yeah.

173
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:13,375
-Stop it.
-Oh, over here.

174
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,625
I'm getting a great shot from here.

175
00:11:17,958 --> 00:11:18,958
Oh, that's awesome.

176
00:11:26,791 --> 00:11:28,000
Yusuke!

177
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:44,708
But it sure is nice here.

178
00:11:44,791 --> 00:11:46,333
What's your favorite part?

179
00:11:46,416 --> 00:11:47,250
Kengo.

180
00:11:47,791 --> 00:11:49,500
My favorite part?

181
00:11:49,583 --> 00:11:50,416
Yeah?

182
00:11:53,208 --> 00:11:54,041
Let's shake hands.

183
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:57,208
Okay? Here.

184
00:12:20,791 --> 00:12:24,166
Come on. You can do it.

185
00:12:28,916 --> 00:12:32,750
You know, if I see
coffee cherries grow on this tree,

186
00:12:33,875 --> 00:12:34,833
I'm going to cry.

187
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:37,250
Yeah, I'm totally going to cry.

188
00:12:42,583 --> 00:12:43,791
Isn't it cute?

189
00:13:31,083 --> 00:13:32,208
Those apples are red.

190
00:13:32,291 --> 00:13:33,750
-You're right!
-Look over there.

191
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:35,500
-There are red apples.
-So pretty.

192
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:36,875
-Look.
-Phew.

193
00:13:36,958 --> 00:13:38,666
Oh, wow!

194
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:40,166
-A centipede?
-Good luck!

195
00:13:40,666 --> 00:13:41,791
Slow down!

196
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:43,291
Be careful.

197
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,583
-Thank you for hosting us again this year.
-Oh, of course.

198
00:13:46,666 --> 00:13:48,666
-We'll be in your care.
-Thank you.

199
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:50,875
The kids were really
looking forward to this.

200
00:13:50,958 --> 00:13:52,541
Hello. Thank you for coming.

201
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:54,291
Thank you.

202
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,791
Wow, these apples look incredible.

203
00:13:57,416 --> 00:13:58,833
They look delicious.

204
00:13:58,916 --> 00:14:00,041
-I know!
-Okay.

205
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:01,958
It's because it's not getting sunlight.

206
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,125
Correct. I'm impressed.

207
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:09,333
Okay, grab this and twist it
so that the sun shines on it. You did it!

208
00:14:09,416 --> 00:14:13,000
Let's clear all the branches here
so that they get plenty of sunlight.

209
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:15,708
Hold on there.

210
00:14:16,375 --> 00:14:17,583
-Wait!
-Watch out!

211
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:20,416
Run away!

212
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:25,416
Watch out!

213
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:29,541
Oh, there you are!

214
00:14:34,333 --> 00:14:35,166
Be careful!

215
00:14:36,958 --> 00:14:37,916
Miki!

216
00:15:09,541 --> 00:15:10,375
Excuse me!

217
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:15,708
Yes? What is it?

218
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:17,500
Um…

219
00:15:18,458 --> 00:15:20,375
Please go out with me.

220
00:15:20,458 --> 00:15:21,916
With intent to marry.

221
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:23,458
Please.

222
00:15:26,333 --> 00:15:27,166
What?

223
00:15:29,125 --> 00:15:31,541
We can get married right away.
I really like you.

224
00:15:33,125 --> 00:15:35,625
I can't hold in my feelings anymore.

225
00:15:39,458 --> 00:15:40,916
Sorry,

226
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:43,916
you should probably give up on me.

227
00:15:44,625 --> 00:15:45,708
I won't.

228
00:15:45,791 --> 00:15:48,333
Wait, I'm happy that you asked, but…

229
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,375
Thank goodness.

230
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:52,000
No, wait.

231
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:55,583
I mean, I'm so plain.

232
00:15:56,250 --> 00:15:59,125
It's okay. I'll stand out
for the both of us.

233
00:16:00,750 --> 00:16:01,583
I'm boring.

234
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:04,791
It's okay. I'm interesting
enough for the both of us.

235
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:09,541
I'm not very dependable.

236
00:16:10,125 --> 00:16:11,750
Or rather, I come off as weak.

237
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,833
See? I'm a man,
but look at how little I eat.

238
00:16:15,541 --> 00:16:18,666
It's okay. I'm strong and dependable.

239
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,208
I eat a bunch too.

240
00:16:24,041 --> 00:16:24,875
Well…

241
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,500
I don't know if you're aware or not…

242
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,333
but I have a weak body.

243
00:16:37,583 --> 00:16:38,416
It's my heart.

244
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:42,208
It's okay. My heart
is strong enough for the both of us.

245
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:44,583
What?

246
00:16:46,125 --> 00:16:46,958
Huh?

247
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:04,125
It seems

248
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:06,958
I have no reason to decline.

249
00:17:09,166 --> 00:17:10,875
After all, for a long time now…

250
00:17:12,583 --> 00:17:14,833
I've had feelings for you.

251
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:18,166
Ever since you were Miss Apple.

252
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:22,166
What?

253
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,875
What?

254
00:17:26,458 --> 00:17:27,500
Are you serious?

255
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:34,791
I'll be in your care.

256
00:17:38,833 --> 00:17:39,916
I'll be in your care.

257
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:48,791
Is it good?

258
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:50,416
-It's tasty!
-Who wants more?

259
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:51,916
Oh, I'll take that.

260
00:17:52,000 --> 00:17:53,541
-Thank you.
-I'll have some.

261
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:54,541
Give me that.

262
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:55,750
Here are some new ones.

263
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:57,750
We still have more.

264
00:17:57,833 --> 00:17:59,625
-Come here.
-Look, I have two!

265
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:13,250
Hey.

266
00:18:13,958 --> 00:18:14,791
What is it?

267
00:18:15,291 --> 00:18:17,583
I'm so happy for Mr. Naruse.

268
00:18:18,708 --> 00:18:19,625
Why's that?

269
00:18:20,166 --> 00:18:21,541
It's such a relief.

270
00:18:22,125 --> 00:18:24,625
Isn't it great how lively he's gotten?

271
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:25,708
Stop it.

272
00:18:26,250 --> 00:18:28,333
Huh? Stop what?

273
00:18:30,041 --> 00:18:32,458
Of course I'm glad he's healthy now.

274
00:18:33,125 --> 00:18:36,333
But stop saying how great it is
that he's more lively.

275
00:18:36,833 --> 00:18:38,750
It implies his old self
wasn't good enough.

276
00:18:38,833 --> 00:18:41,333
Come on. That's not what I meant.

277
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,416
That's what it ends up meaning!

278
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:48,583
I fell in love with and married him
when he wasn't as lively or healthy.

279
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:50,208
It's an insult to me.

280
00:18:50,958 --> 00:18:52,541
Is that what I'm doing?

281
00:18:52,625 --> 00:18:53,625
It is!

282
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:58,041
So, stop saying
that you're glad he's lively now.

283
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:00,791
Okay.

284
00:19:01,666 --> 00:19:02,500
I'm sorry.

285
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:06,333
Wow, isn't it great
how lively Naruse has gotten?

286
00:19:06,416 --> 00:19:09,541
-Ms. Tada was saying…
-He's like a different person.

287
00:19:09,625 --> 00:19:11,958
They want to come back in the fall.

288
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,416
-So good.
-We ate a lot, huh?

289
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:23,083
-It's great!
-Hm? It sure is, isn't it?

290
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,375
-Huh?
-About the other day…

291
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,416
I sincerely apologize.

292
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:56,125
Oh, don't say that. I was also--

293
00:19:56,208 --> 00:19:58,208
No, I'm the one at fault.

294
00:19:58,291 --> 00:20:00,041
You did nothing wrong.

295
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:02,750
I really didn't want to leave you thinking

296
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,083
that I'm an overly sensitive,
egotistical lady.

297
00:20:05,166 --> 00:20:08,833
You were kind enough
to make coffee for us like that.

298
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:11,166
I'm truly sorry for spoiling everything.

299
00:20:11,250 --> 00:20:12,916
No, but…

300
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:16,333
Don't say you did anything wrong.
I'm the only one who acted poorly.

301
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,208
Okay, I understand.

302
00:20:20,416 --> 00:20:22,333
Sorry for acting scary during my apology.

303
00:20:23,166 --> 00:20:24,750
Oh, it's fine.

304
00:20:26,583 --> 00:20:27,916
Would you like to sit?

305
00:20:37,291 --> 00:20:39,875
Um, my name is Naruse.

306
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:42,208
Nice to meet you.

307
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,000
I live in Niseko.

308
00:20:45,583 --> 00:20:47,791
My wife's family owns an apple farm there.

309
00:20:48,291 --> 00:20:49,125
I see.

310
00:20:50,916 --> 00:20:52,416
It's nice to meet you.

311
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,458
I'm Sugawara.

312
00:20:56,375 --> 00:20:57,833
I get on at Rankoshi Station,

313
00:20:57,916 --> 00:21:00,541
but I only recently started living there.

314
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:03,166
Oh, are you from Otaru then?

315
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:06,458
No, I was born and raised in Tokyo.
My parents are still there.

316
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:10,375
After some twists and turns,
I ended up finding a job here.

317
00:21:11,083 --> 00:21:11,958
I see.

318
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:19,958
Oh, no.
I don't think I can hold my tongue.

319
00:21:20,916 --> 00:21:22,916
-Huh?
-Well, you see.

320
00:21:23,416 --> 00:21:26,708
I actually work in the coffee business.

321
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:28,458
Wow.

322
00:21:29,750 --> 00:21:30,583
Wait.

323
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:35,000
Are you a coffee expert then?

324
00:21:35,083 --> 00:21:37,291
Oh, well, yes.

325
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:40,250
Man, you should've said so sooner.

326
00:21:40,333 --> 00:21:43,000
I ended up lecturing you about coffee.

327
00:21:43,083 --> 00:21:44,708
When would I have told you?

328
00:21:44,791 --> 00:21:46,708
That's true, but…

329
00:21:47,291 --> 00:21:49,833
Does that mean
you're an expert at making coffee?

330
00:21:50,416 --> 00:21:51,583
Yes, that's right.

331
00:21:51,666 --> 00:21:54,791
Jeez, I bet
I was really bad at making coffee.

332
00:21:54,875 --> 00:21:56,208
Yes, it was horrible.

333
00:21:59,166 --> 00:22:00,375
I'm sure it was.

334
00:22:00,458 --> 00:22:01,583
I'm so embarrassed.

335
00:22:02,541 --> 00:22:04,291
-I'm sorry.
-It's fine.

336
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:09,375
Can I give you a tip
on how to make good coffee?

337
00:22:09,875 --> 00:22:11,125
Yes, please.

338
00:22:11,666 --> 00:22:14,083
-First, let's say that this is a dripper.
-Okay.

339
00:22:14,583 --> 00:22:16,583
Pour hot water from the center

340
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:21,208
and move gently like this,
allowing it to take in the water.

341
00:22:21,291 --> 00:22:22,125
Right.

342
00:22:27,541 --> 00:22:29,125
-Goodbye then.
-Goodbye.

343
00:22:29,875 --> 00:22:31,458
-Have a good day.
-You too.

344
00:22:56,458 --> 00:22:57,458
Excuse me.

345
00:23:00,250 --> 00:23:01,250
Oh, hello.

346
00:23:03,375 --> 00:23:04,458
How can I help you?

347
00:23:04,541 --> 00:23:07,166
-I have a question about this.
-Okay.

348
00:23:09,916 --> 00:23:10,750
Excuse me.

349
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,083
Excuse me.

350
00:23:13,833 --> 00:23:14,666
Coming.

351
00:23:34,375 --> 00:23:36,125
Is this what she meant?

352
00:23:42,083 --> 00:23:44,083
Everyone, please have some.

353
00:23:44,583 --> 00:23:46,875
I tried making some coffee.

354
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:48,500
-Really?
-Oh, wow.

355
00:23:48,583 --> 00:23:49,541
Thank you!

356
00:23:49,625 --> 00:23:51,708
-Are you sure? Thank you!
-Go ahead.

357
00:23:51,791 --> 00:23:52,791
Wow. Coffee?

358
00:23:53,833 --> 00:23:55,416
-What a nice aroma.
-What's this?

359
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:57,083
I tried making some coffee.

360
00:23:57,166 --> 00:23:58,166
It's good.

361
00:23:58,250 --> 00:23:59,500
-It's great.
-Really?

362
00:23:59,583 --> 00:24:01,958
It's like coffee from a café.

363
00:24:02,583 --> 00:24:03,416
It's so good.

364
00:24:04,333 --> 00:24:06,125
-Isn't it?
-Yeah.

365
00:24:07,625 --> 00:24:09,333
I feel so relaxed.

366
00:24:09,416 --> 00:24:11,875
Mm-hmm, this is good.

367
00:24:11,958 --> 00:24:12,791
It's delicious.

