370
00:24:22,958 --> 00:24:24,833
Oh, hello. Good to see you.

371
00:24:24,916 --> 00:24:26,166
Good to see you too.

372
00:24:26,250 --> 00:24:29,041
What a coincidence,
running into each other twice in one day.

373
00:24:29,125 --> 00:24:31,333
Well, there's only one train an hour.

374
00:24:31,416 --> 00:24:32,583
Oh, that's true.

375
00:25:00,458 --> 00:25:03,250
I'm jealous.
I want to go back to those days.

376
00:25:04,125 --> 00:25:07,208
No, it's really hard
for students nowadays,

377
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:09,458
with job hunting and such.

378
00:25:10,250 --> 00:25:13,833
Why did you decide to work for
a coffee company, Ms. Sugawara?

379
00:25:15,666 --> 00:25:17,125
It's a long story. Is that okay?

380
00:25:17,208 --> 00:25:18,458
Yes, I'm curious.

381
00:25:19,416 --> 00:25:21,375
Our company's interesting.

382
00:25:21,875 --> 00:25:26,291
All the employees are people
who have been saved by coffee once.

383
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:28,250
Wow.

384
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:31,583
Saved by coffee…

385
00:25:31,666 --> 00:25:32,791
I see.

386
00:25:32,875 --> 00:25:35,791
You make a good
conversation partner, Mr. Naruse.

387
00:25:36,291 --> 00:25:37,125
Huh?

388
00:25:37,208 --> 00:25:41,166
I kept saying we should keep going,
but they insisted we leave.

389
00:25:41,791 --> 00:25:43,500
So I said I'd go alone.

390
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,541
I asked which way to go
and started walking.

391
00:25:47,375 --> 00:25:48,833
Then, before I knew it,

392
00:25:48,916 --> 00:25:51,750
I was lost in the mountains of Costa Rica.

393
00:25:51,833 --> 00:25:53,666
Jungle as far as the eye can see.

394
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:54,791
That's crazy.

395
00:25:54,875 --> 00:25:57,083
I was like, "Where are we?"

396
00:25:59,500 --> 00:26:00,625
Wanna sit here?

397
00:26:01,208 --> 00:26:02,041
Excuse me.

398
00:26:02,958 --> 00:26:04,166
Oh, wow.

399
00:26:07,250 --> 00:26:09,250
They're flirting on the train.

400
00:26:09,333 --> 00:26:10,416
No, we're not.

401
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:12,291
-Are you flirting?
-No, no.

402
00:26:14,125 --> 00:26:15,958
-We're not.
-Lovey-dovey!

403
00:26:16,041 --> 00:26:18,916
Hey, stop that! I'm sorry.

404
00:26:33,416 --> 00:26:34,250
Huh?

405
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:38,333
Good evening.

406
00:26:41,375 --> 00:26:43,375
I wanted to hear the rest of your story.

407
00:27:54,041 --> 00:27:56,958
I found out there's a plan

408
00:27:57,458 --> 00:27:59,583
to hold a surprise birthday party for me.

409
00:28:00,375 --> 00:28:03,000
Oh, now I see.

410
00:28:03,083 --> 00:28:04,250
Wait. When is it?

411
00:28:04,875 --> 00:28:06,458
Well, it's tomorrow.

412
00:28:06,541 --> 00:28:08,333
-I see.
-But that's beside the point.

413
00:28:08,416 --> 00:28:11,583
I overheard them planning the surprise.

414
00:28:12,125 --> 00:28:13,708
What do I do?

415
00:28:13,791 --> 00:28:18,041
Should I pretend like I didn't know
and just act surprised?

416
00:28:18,125 --> 00:28:18,958
What do you think?

417
00:28:19,041 --> 00:28:21,041
Well…

418
00:28:21,708 --> 00:28:25,458
Maybe you should act surprised
and pretend like you didn't notice,

419
00:28:25,541 --> 00:28:27,125
since they went to the trouble.

420
00:28:28,208 --> 00:28:29,916
-Right.
-Yeah.

421
00:28:34,333 --> 00:28:35,166
Actually…

422
00:28:36,916 --> 00:28:38,000
That's not right.

423
00:28:39,375 --> 00:28:40,208
It's not?

424
00:28:41,208 --> 00:28:43,708
That's what the usual me would do.

425
00:28:47,458 --> 00:28:48,750
But it should be more fun.

426
00:28:49,333 --> 00:28:50,291
Huh?

427
00:28:50,375 --> 00:28:52,625
Pretend you didn't notice, act surprised,

428
00:28:52,708 --> 00:28:54,375
and party as hard as you can.

429
00:28:54,458 --> 00:28:56,250
Then, when the party's heating up,

430
00:28:56,333 --> 00:29:00,208
create your own surprise
by saying, "Actually, I already knew."

431
00:29:00,708 --> 00:29:03,416
Then, give everyone a small present.

432
00:29:03,916 --> 00:29:05,583
That should liven things up.

433
00:29:07,333 --> 00:29:09,041
-I see.
-Yeah.

434
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:13,416
Thank you.

435
00:29:14,291 --> 00:29:15,416
I'll give it a try.

436
00:29:16,083 --> 00:29:17,041
Good luck.

437
00:29:17,541 --> 00:29:18,375
Thank you.

438
00:29:19,958 --> 00:29:22,291
Now that I know, happy birthd--

439
00:29:22,375 --> 00:29:23,416
No, not yet.

440
00:29:24,208 --> 00:29:27,083
You shouldn't say that stuff early.

441
00:29:27,666 --> 00:29:30,208
If you say it early,
you lose the chance to say it later.

442
00:29:31,666 --> 00:29:33,791
Okay, got it.

443
00:29:34,875 --> 00:29:36,833
In that case, I'll say it tomorrow.

444
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:39,250
Thank you.

445
00:29:47,166 --> 00:29:48,000
What's wrong?

446
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:50,833
Oh, nothing.

447
00:29:51,833 --> 00:29:52,916
It's just that…

448
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:55,708
I felt something strange.

449
00:29:55,791 --> 00:29:57,416
I don't know how to describe it.

450
00:30:02,166 --> 00:30:03,041
Sorry about that.

451
00:30:35,541 --> 00:30:37,541
Sorry for asking so suddenly.

452
00:30:38,541 --> 00:30:39,958
Is missing work really okay?

453
00:30:40,041 --> 00:30:41,708
Yeah. It's totally fine.

454
00:30:42,791 --> 00:30:46,416
Leave it to them
to both get a fever at the same time.

455
00:30:48,375 --> 00:30:51,625
Still, I'm excited
for my very first farm show.

456
00:30:52,416 --> 00:30:53,250
Yeah.

457
00:30:54,250 --> 00:30:55,083
Thank you.

458
00:31:26,541 --> 00:31:27,541
Are you okay?

459
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,791
Yeah, I'm fine.

460
00:31:31,708 --> 00:31:34,083
It's been a while since our last outing.

461
00:31:34,583 --> 00:31:35,541
Yeah.

462
00:32:20,708 --> 00:32:23,750
Kazu! Are you okay?

463
00:32:25,041 --> 00:32:26,000
Can you breathe?

464
00:32:26,958 --> 00:32:29,083
Kazu, stay calm.

465
00:32:30,125 --> 00:32:31,208
Are you okay?

